test: expand daemon integration tests for executor registration (he-0r8.2)

Add test doubles (stubDaemonTool, makeStubTools, makeFailingTools) and
registerExecutors helper to test config-driven executor registration
without real postgres or external services.

New test coverage:
- TestRegistration_AllDisabled: baseline with only local+entities
- TestRegistration_AllEnabled: all 9 executors with correct tool counts
- TestRegistration_Partial: selective enablement (memory+comms only)
- TestRegistration_MCPRequiresServers: MCP needs servers configured
- TestToolDefsExcludeDisabledExecutors: disabled executor tools hidden
- TestToolDefsReappearAfterReset: reset re-enables executor tools
- TestCoordToAgentTools: coordToAgentTools bridge correctness
- TestCoordToAgentToolsExecute: end-to-end stub tool execution
- TestSimpleExecutor: simpleExecutor Name/Tools methods
- TestRegistrationToolCounts: table-driven config combinations
- TestDaemonStopIdempotent: Stop on never-started daemon
- TestDaemonNewFields: New constructor field assignment
- TestGracefulShutdownSequence: all executors disabled = empty ToolDefs

Fix compilation errors in prior test skeleton (tools.FailableCall,
missing sort import).
